OL,3,CSmall improvement in quality of
OL,4,Cbathing waters rated 'excellent' or
OL,5,C'good'
OL,7,FNearly nine out of ten (87%) of
OL,8,FEngland's natural bathing waters have
OL,9,Fbeen classed as "excellent" or "good"
OL,10,Fby the Environment Agency,
OL,11,Frepresenting a slight improvement on
OL,12,Flast year's number.
OL,14,FOverall, 93% or 417 tested sites rated
OL,15,Fexcellent, good or sufficient, a
OL,16,Fslight rise on 2024, and the number of
OL,17,F"excellent" rated bathing sites on
OL,18,Fbeaches, lakes and rivers was up from
OL,19,F289 last year to 297 in 2025,
OL,20,Faccording to the latest figures from
OL,21,Fthe Environment Agency.
