OL,3,CSmall improvement in quality of
OL,4,Cbathing waters rated 'excellent' or
OL,5,C'good'
OL,7,FThey include ending the rule that
OL,8,Fautomatically removes a bathing
OL,9,Fwater's status after five years of
OL,10,F'poor' ratings in a row. Regulators
OL,11,Fnow look at struggling sites and,
OL,12,Fwhere possible, work towards finding
OL,13,Frealistic options for improving them.
OL,15,FThe reforms also include bringing in
OL,16,Fmore flexibility to monitoring dates,
OL,17,Fso that testing can be adapted to suit
OL,18,Findividual sites and better match when
OL,19,Fpeople actually use the water.
